==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Periculum
<hw>Pe*ric"u*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pericula</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. &
O.Eng. Law)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Danger; risk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a narrower, judicial sense: Accident or
<xex>casus</xex>, as distinguished from <xex>dolus</xex> and
<xex>culpa</xex>, and hence relieving one from the duty of performing an
obligation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pericystitis</ent>⟦br⟧
